article.headline: Taylor's 20 points help Gauchos trounce Vandals
article.linkText: Taylor's 20 points help Gauchos trounce Vandals
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Lindsay Taylor scored 20 points on 8-of-10 shooting as UC Santa Barbara (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat Idaho 71-42 on Saturday night.

The Gauchos (10-2, 3-0 Big West Conference) won their fifth
straight. All five wins have been by at least 14 points. 

Mia Fisher had 13 points for UC Santa Barbara. Lisa Willett and Brandy Richardson added 11 each.

Autumn Fielding led Idaho (4-10, 2-2) with 12 points.

UC Santa Barbara shot 65.2 percent from the field on the way to a 37-18 halftime lead.

The Gauchos shot 60.9 percent and were 6-for-9 (66.7 percent) from behind the 3-point line.

Idaho shot just 25.9 percent from the field.
